WEBVTT

00:03.046 --> 00:04.395
This...
[ Gun cocks ]

00:04.439 --> 00:05.440
...is for Mason.

00:05.483 --> 00:07.181
Veer: Just kill my son.

00:07.224 --> 00:09.966
He's the one responsible
for your son's death.

00:10.010 --> 00:11.881
[ Gunshot ]

00:11.924 --> 00:14.275
Ren: Jag is in the hospital
with a bullet in his chest.

00:14.318 --> 00:14.971
What happened
out there?

00:15.015 --> 00:15.928
He didn't tell you?

00:15.972 --> 00:18.496
Insurance release for Jag.

00:18.540 --> 00:21.195
They need a family member
to sign.

00:21.238 --> 00:22.239
Ren:
Where's my father?

00:22.283 --> 00:23.849
Can't help you.
It's fine.

00:23.893 --> 00:25.155
I'll have Travis
look into it.

00:25.199 --> 00:26.330
I know
he used to be a cop,

00:26.374 --> 00:27.679
but now he works for me.

00:27.723 --> 00:30.291
County's bringing someone in
to be acting sheriff

00:30.334 --> 00:32.945
while I'm down.I don't need any help.

00:32.989 --> 00:34.643
Yeah, you do.

00:34.686 --> 00:35.992
Scarlet: I have information
that you want.

00:36.036 --> 00:37.646
I want to make a trade.

00:37.689 --> 00:39.735
Wolf told us about his deal
with the Syndicate.

00:39.778 --> 00:42.346
If you run, they will find you.

00:42.390 --> 00:44.131
Humbert: We know you made a copy
of something

00:44.174 --> 00:46.002
that wasn't yours.

00:46.046 --> 00:48.048
You need to tell me
where it is.

00:49.614 --> 00:51.660
Scarlet.

00:51.703 --> 00:53.096
Cassie: Phoebe deserves more
out of this life.

00:53.140 --> 00:55.359
Give Phoebe up.
It's your only good option.

00:55.403 --> 00:57.057
Scarlet: Ohh.Humbert: Oh, my goodness.

01:05.761 --> 01:08.807
[ Indistinct conversations ]

01:08.851 --> 01:10.157
What are we doing here?

01:10.200 --> 01:11.941
Scarlet: Just need to grab
something real quick.

01:11.984 --> 01:13.725
In and out.

01:13.769 --> 01:14.987
Nancy is waiting.
I'll let you...

01:15.031 --> 01:16.380
I'm hungry.

01:16.424 --> 01:18.556
I know, sweetheart.
I am, too.

01:18.600 --> 01:20.167
♪♪

01:20.210 --> 01:22.560
[ Laughing ]
That's what I said!

01:22.604 --> 01:24.127
Um, what are you
in the mood for, huh?

01:24.171 --> 01:27.348
Uh, pizza, barbecue?

01:27.391 --> 01:29.219
Um, cheeseburgers.

01:29.263 --> 01:31.265
Cheeseburgers!
Now we're talking.

01:31.308 --> 01:37.706
♪♪

01:37.749 --> 01:44.321
♪♪

01:44.365 --> 01:46.149
Are we going home now?[ Locker closes ]

01:46.193 --> 01:48.020
Yes, yes.
Soon, sweetheart.

01:48.064 --> 01:50.153
We are gonna go up
to Canada.

01:50.197 --> 01:53.287
But first I need to take care
of a little something, okay?

01:53.330 --> 01:54.984
Okay.

01:55.027 --> 02:02.644
♪♪

02:02.687 --> 02:10.434
♪♪

02:12.262 --> 02:15.352
You know...

02:15.396 --> 02:17.398
maybe it's better
if I go in alone.

02:17.441 --> 02:20.227
Well, if it were me, I would
want to see a friendly face.

02:24.361 --> 02:25.449
Shall we?

02:30.672 --> 02:32.282
Look who I found.

02:34.458 --> 02:36.939
Hello, son.

02:40.247 --> 02:41.596
How ya feeling?

02:41.639 --> 02:43.902
Okay,
all things considered.

02:45.339 --> 02:47.210
You almost
got me killed.

02:47.254 --> 02:49.212
Ialmost got you killed?

02:49.256 --> 02:52.128
That --
That's not what happened.

02:52.172 --> 02:54.086
So what did happen?

02:54.130 --> 02:55.871
Jag, do you want to say it,
just so we can both hear it?

02:55.914 --> 02:57.568
Yeah, well,
dear old dad here

02:57.612 --> 02:59.309
decided to offer up my life
for his.

02:59.353 --> 03:01.355
No.

03:01.398 --> 03:02.486
That's not
what I was doing.

03:02.530 --> 03:03.792
I was going to get help.

03:03.835 --> 03:06.142
Yeah, for yourself,
maybe.

03:06.186 --> 03:08.057
You left me there
and I got shot.

03:08.100 --> 03:09.363
No, you got it wrong,
son.

03:09.406 --> 03:10.929
So tomato,
tomah-toh then.

03:10.973 --> 03:13.018
That's enough, Reenu.

03:13.062 --> 03:15.934
All that talk..

03:15.978 --> 03:19.286
about family...

03:19.329 --> 03:20.722
was just a lie.

03:22.637 --> 03:27.119
You tried to save yourself
by abandoning your son.

03:27.163 --> 03:28.469
That's what happened.

03:28.512 --> 03:30.297
I won't be mocked.

03:32.429 --> 03:34.649
You two need to know
who's in charge here.

03:34.692 --> 03:36.346
I know who's in charge.

03:39.654 --> 03:43.179
I have nothing more
to say here.

03:43.223 --> 03:44.267
[ Grunts ]

03:44.311 --> 03:53.494
♪♪

03:53.537 --> 03:55.409
Hey.

03:55.452 --> 03:57.672
You need to be careful.I got this.

03:57.715 --> 03:59.195
You rest up.

04:03.895 --> 04:05.201
[ Trunk closes ]

04:05.245 --> 04:08.552
Cassie,
good to have you back.

04:08.596 --> 04:09.684
I'll see ya in there.

04:09.727 --> 04:12.077
Beau: Hey, you,
in the boots!

04:12.121 --> 04:13.775
You know anything
about cars?

04:13.818 --> 04:16.517
Power steering pump,
particularly.

04:16.560 --> 04:19.346
[ Grunts ]
This thing is just...

04:21.130 --> 04:22.523
Oh.

04:22.566 --> 04:24.220
[ Chuckles ]

04:24.264 --> 04:25.743
Sorry, I thought
you were a guy.

04:25.787 --> 04:27.528
The -- The boots.

04:27.571 --> 04:30.444
Oh, so I can't help you
with the car.

04:30.487 --> 04:32.315
Well, come on, girls don't know
anything about cars.

04:32.359 --> 04:33.490
Excuse me.

04:33.534 --> 04:34.491
Move to the side,
please.

04:34.535 --> 04:35.318
Okay.

04:37.146 --> 04:38.365
That's your pump
right there.

04:44.066 --> 04:45.676
Son of a bitch.

04:45.720 --> 04:47.417
You're good.
Yeah.

04:47.461 --> 04:50.072
Okay, but the --
the leak's coming from...

04:51.987 --> 04:53.467
The leak
is coming from underneath there,

04:53.510 --> 04:55.556
and so I just...

04:55.599 --> 04:58.210
Truth is, I'm worried about it
getting in the waterways.

04:58.254 --> 05:01.779
It's bad for the trout,
conservation, all that.

05:01.823 --> 05:04.347
So, you fish?

05:04.391 --> 05:05.348
Fish?

05:05.392 --> 05:06.915
Yeah.

05:06.958 --> 05:08.612
Fish --
that's with a fishing pole?

05:08.656 --> 05:10.962
[ Laughs ]

05:11.006 --> 05:12.268
Okay, you're funny.

05:12.312 --> 05:13.574
I'm being an ass.

05:13.617 --> 05:15.489
Sorry. Beau Arlen.

05:15.532 --> 05:16.838
Cassie Dewell.

05:16.881 --> 05:18.579
I know who you are.

05:18.622 --> 05:20.755
You do?

05:20.798 --> 05:22.365
Well, it's a small town.

05:22.409 --> 05:25.499
And law enforcement's
one big, not so happy,

05:25.542 --> 05:27.065
dysfunctional family,
right?

05:27.109 --> 05:28.937
Yeah.
You in law enforcement?

05:28.980 --> 05:32.549
Mm, well, I was --
in Houston.
Mm.

05:32.593 --> 05:35.378
But then I'm sorta retired --
well, on the bench.

05:35.422 --> 05:37.641
Fishing.

05:37.685 --> 05:40.078
But now I'm un-retired,
so...

05:40.122 --> 05:41.558
Stepping in
for Sheriff Tubb?

05:41.602 --> 05:43.255
You are good.

05:43.299 --> 05:44.648
Small town, right?

05:44.692 --> 05:46.041
Okay.
Yeah.

05:46.084 --> 05:47.303
Well,
good luck with that.

05:47.347 --> 05:48.870
Jenny Hoyt,
she's my old partner.

05:48.913 --> 05:51.525
Oh, yeah.
Yeah, I heard about Jenny Hoyt.

05:51.568 --> 05:52.526
I can handle her.

05:52.569 --> 05:54.615
[ Laughs ]

05:54.658 --> 05:55.833
You keep thinking that.

05:55.877 --> 05:57.531
Um...have a good day.

05:57.574 --> 06:00.664
Oh, yeah --
the weekly hankie meeting.

06:00.708 --> 06:02.623
I hear it helps.

06:02.666 --> 06:04.189
You going to that, too,
or are you just here

06:04.233 --> 06:06.496
to get some dirt
on Jenny Hoyt?

06:06.540 --> 06:07.845
[ Laughs ]

06:07.889 --> 06:11.458
No, no, I keep trying
to go in there,

06:11.501 --> 06:13.285
but something always seems
to stop me.

06:16.506 --> 06:18.769
Today it was Pedro.

06:18.813 --> 06:20.597
Sprung a leak on me.

06:20.641 --> 06:23.034
You really don't know anything
about cars, do you?

06:23.078 --> 06:25.341
I don't. Could you
give me a hand, please?

06:25.385 --> 06:29.345
♪♪

06:29.389 --> 06:30.781
[ Sighs ]

06:30.825 --> 06:31.608
Okay,
I'll help you out.

06:31.652 --> 06:33.480
Okay.

06:33.523 --> 06:35.351
Yeah.
Alright.

06:35.395 --> 06:37.832
Alright, Pedro. Her hands are
gonna be softer than mine.

06:37.875 --> 06:38.876
Maybe.

06:38.920 --> 06:40.443
[ Laughs ]

06:40.487 --> 06:43.490
♪♪

06:43.533 --> 06:44.491
[ Door opens ]

06:45.927 --> 06:47.145
Denise: Oh, hey.
You're back.

06:47.189 --> 06:48.886
Yeah,
and working on no sleep.

06:48.930 --> 06:50.497
Where's Cassie?

06:50.540 --> 06:51.672
Jenny's.
She should be back soon.

06:51.715 --> 06:53.108
So what's going on?

06:53.151 --> 06:55.023
Where's Jerrie?

06:55.066 --> 06:56.459
She's still in Idaho working
with local law enforcement.

06:56.503 --> 06:58.679
We confirmed multiple sightings
of Scarlet,

06:58.722 --> 07:00.028
and the hope is
she's still there.

07:00.071 --> 07:01.638
Did you hear
that she called Cassie?

07:01.682 --> 07:03.684
Yeah. Why do you think
I rushed back?

07:03.727 --> 07:05.947
Aww,
you're worried about her.

07:05.990 --> 07:06.948
How sweet.

07:06.991 --> 07:08.602
More like smart.

07:08.645 --> 07:09.820
Scarlet's a sociopath.

07:09.864 --> 07:12.475
Still sweet.

07:12.519 --> 07:14.738
So you really think that Scarlet
would go after Cassie?

07:14.782 --> 07:16.610
[ Sighs ] I don't know.

07:16.653 --> 07:18.742
But if she does come back here,
she might have company.

07:18.786 --> 07:21.832
When Jerrie and I were
confirming those sightings,

07:21.876 --> 07:24.095
we learned someone else
had come looking for Scarlet.

07:24.139 --> 07:26.750
Oh, you think it was someone
from the Syndicate.

07:26.794 --> 07:28.317
I think it's a possibility.Just like you think

07:28.360 --> 07:30.537
the Syndicate
may have taken out Wolf.

07:30.580 --> 07:31.755
Crazy?

07:31.799 --> 07:33.757
Not at all.

07:33.801 --> 07:36.020
I was looking for some things
when you were gone.

07:38.458 --> 07:40.547
Julian McGill.

07:40.590 --> 07:43.332
Who is he?EMT that worked on Wolf
when he died.

07:43.375 --> 07:45.160
According
to the hospital paperwork.

07:45.203 --> 07:46.727
Did you call him
to confirm that?

07:46.770 --> 07:47.989
See, that's where
this gets interesting.

07:48.032 --> 07:50.078
Mr. Julian there
isn't answering his phone,

07:50.121 --> 07:52.297
and apparently he hasn't been
showing up to work lately.

07:52.341 --> 07:54.169
Now, that isinteresting.

07:54.212 --> 07:56.301
Mm-hmm, maybe you and Cassie
should run by his place

07:56.345 --> 07:57.955
and check things out.

07:57.999 --> 08:00.001
Kiss her first, though.

08:00.044 --> 08:03.526
♪♪

08:03.570 --> 08:05.136
-Hey.
-Hey.

08:05.180 --> 08:06.790
I was on my way
to the office.[ Door closes ]

08:06.834 --> 08:08.009
I figured I'd stop by,
see how you were doing.

08:08.052 --> 08:09.532
Uh, not good.

08:09.576 --> 08:10.533
Travis?

08:10.577 --> 08:11.665
Ghosted me.

08:11.708 --> 08:13.362
[ Sighs ]

08:13.405 --> 08:14.755
Hey, you talk to Tubb?

08:14.798 --> 08:16.321
Not today. Why?

08:16.365 --> 08:17.584
I ran into
his replacement earlier.

08:17.627 --> 08:19.107
What?

08:19.150 --> 08:20.891
Yeah, Beau something.

08:20.935 --> 08:22.806
Tubb did say he was gonna
bring someone to help,

08:22.850 --> 08:24.634
but that was fast.

08:24.678 --> 08:25.592
Yeah, good luck.

08:25.635 --> 08:27.245
He seems, um...

08:27.289 --> 08:29.030
Temporary?

08:29.073 --> 08:31.815
No, I wouldn't say that.
He's just very Texas

08:31.859 --> 08:34.601
or Houston --
one of those kinds.

08:34.644 --> 08:38.387
Hmm. So, wait,
where did you meet him?

08:38.430 --> 08:40.824
I was on my way
to this grief counseling meeting

08:40.868 --> 08:42.217
I started going to.
He said he was there for that,

08:42.260 --> 08:44.001
but...
Hmm.

08:44.045 --> 08:45.786
Maybe he can help me
with Travis.

08:45.829 --> 08:47.614
You still think he's planning
on killing Veer?

08:47.657 --> 08:49.790
I didn't say that.

08:49.833 --> 08:51.835
Jenny, come on. We both know
that's what he wants.

08:54.055 --> 08:55.839
Maybe, but...

08:55.883 --> 08:57.928
[ Sighs ]
Ren know's he's a cop,

08:57.972 --> 08:59.669
and I've been to his handler
at State

08:59.713 --> 09:02.759
and he's dead weight
as far as they're concerned.

09:02.803 --> 09:04.239
I have to do something.

09:04.282 --> 09:06.937
Arrest Veer.

09:06.981 --> 09:08.286
Take away his target.

09:10.854 --> 09:11.594
Thank you.

09:13.465 --> 09:14.684
That's why I love you.

09:14.728 --> 09:16.643
Yep.

09:16.686 --> 09:18.209
[ Door opens ]

09:22.779 --> 09:24.868
What was that?

09:24.912 --> 09:28.742
I wanted to see if maybe,
just maybe,

09:28.785 --> 09:30.787
you'd be a father
for once.

09:42.669 --> 09:46.455
Get in the car
and stop this nonsense.

09:46.498 --> 09:50.459
♪♪

09:50.502 --> 09:51.721
[ Gun cocks ]

09:51.765 --> 09:56.857
♪♪

09:56.900 --> 09:58.859
I love you, Daddy.

09:58.902 --> 10:05.561
♪♪

10:05.605 --> 10:11.872
♪♪

10:17.007 --> 10:20.097
Alright. Listen, I'm here
because Sheriff Tubb
asked me to step in.

10:20.141 --> 10:21.751
Now, I am new here, okay?

10:21.795 --> 10:23.492
Six months in Montana,
Texas before that.

10:23.535 --> 10:24.667
And what I don't know
about how things work

10:24.711 --> 10:26.147
here in Big Sky Country,

10:26.190 --> 10:27.757
well, I'll just fake it
until I make it.

10:27.801 --> 10:30.673
[ Laughs ][ Laughs ]

10:30.717 --> 10:32.936
[ Whistles, clears throat ]

10:32.980 --> 10:34.938
Now, you are all free
to check my bonafides.

10:34.982 --> 10:36.113
I will admit there are
some things in there

10:36.157 --> 10:37.898
that I'm not
exactly proud of,

10:37.941 --> 10:39.160
but I am here to help.
Okay?

10:39.203 --> 10:41.945
Get things moving
in the right direction.

10:41.989 --> 10:44.513
And as John Prine says,
"Catch a few fish."

10:44.556 --> 10:46.820
[ Laughs ]
Sir.

10:46.863 --> 10:48.038
Call me Beau, yeah.Right, Beau.

10:48.082 --> 10:50.388
Deputy --Poppernak, three P's, sir.

10:50.432 --> 10:51.955
[ Door opens ]Um, yeah, my brother,

10:51.999 --> 10:53.914
he's got, uh, two miles of
pristine trout stream

10:53.957 --> 10:55.045
going right through
his property...[ Door closes ]

10:55.089 --> 10:56.960
...and it would be
an honor

10:57.004 --> 10:58.832
to take you and
[clicks tongue] hook you up.

10:58.875 --> 10:59.833
[ Chuckles ]
Not a joke.

10:59.876 --> 11:01.399
Are you sucking up?

11:01.443 --> 11:03.924
Sounds to me
like you're sucking up.

11:03.967 --> 11:05.795
Let me tell you
something...

11:05.839 --> 11:06.840
I like it.

11:06.883 --> 11:09.756
100% approve, okay?

11:09.799 --> 11:11.845
'Course I trust you know
there's a line there, too.

11:14.238 --> 11:17.285
Well, you must be Miss Hoyt.

11:17.328 --> 11:19.069
And you must be
the new temporary sheriff.

11:19.113 --> 11:21.071
Yeah, I was just giving
a little bit

11:21.115 --> 11:22.594
of an orientation
type thing.

11:22.638 --> 11:23.770
I guess you didn't get
the memo

11:23.813 --> 11:25.423
I'd be addressing
the troops.

11:25.467 --> 11:27.774
Nope.

11:27.817 --> 11:29.514
So what did I miss?

11:29.558 --> 11:33.997
Well, uh, Deputy Poppa--
Poppa Smurf -- Pop--

11:34.041 --> 11:36.434
Poppernak.Yeah, Poppernak over here

11:36.478 --> 11:38.741
was just telling me about
a sweet fishing honey hole.

11:38.785 --> 11:40.003
He was sucking up.

11:40.047 --> 11:41.004
It worked.

11:41.048 --> 11:42.136
I like him.

11:42.179 --> 11:44.007
[ Telephone rings ]

11:44.051 --> 11:45.313
Sorry.

11:45.356 --> 11:47.794
Team Hoyt.
Team Hoyt.

11:47.837 --> 11:50.971
Anyway, would you like me
to start from the top?

11:51.014 --> 11:54.148
I would like a word.

11:54.191 --> 11:55.540
In private.

11:55.584 --> 12:00.154
♪♪

12:00.197 --> 12:01.851
[ Indistinct conversations ]

12:01.895 --> 12:03.026
How you wanna do this,
darlin'?

12:03.070 --> 12:04.985
Darling?

12:05.028 --> 12:06.116
Gotta be kidding me.[ Door closes ]

12:06.160 --> 12:07.814
Come on.
I didn't mean nothing by it.

12:07.857 --> 12:09.598
I mean, is -- is it
all nicknames

12:09.641 --> 12:10.904
that you take offense to,
or just "darling"?

12:10.947 --> 12:11.774
'Cause I gotta be honest,

12:11.818 --> 12:12.993
where I come from --
Texas --

12:13.036 --> 12:14.342
everybody has
a nickname.

12:14.385 --> 12:15.473
Mine's BT, actually.

12:15.517 --> 12:16.779
You can call me Hoyt.

12:16.823 --> 12:19.869
Okay, Hoyt.

12:19.913 --> 12:22.829
Listen, I'm just trying to put
everybody at ease, okay?

12:22.872 --> 12:25.135
Get to know my team.

12:25.179 --> 12:27.659
Tubb called, I answered.
Here I am.

12:27.703 --> 12:29.400
He also said you might be
a little red-assed

12:29.444 --> 12:31.402
that you're not put
in charge, which --

12:31.446 --> 12:33.013
And I gotta say
I double copy you on that.

12:33.056 --> 12:35.406
Wow, you're a real chatty one,
aren't you?

12:35.450 --> 12:36.886
Not what I expected.

12:36.930 --> 12:37.844
Shoot,
you should meet my brother.

12:37.887 --> 12:39.497
[ Laughs ]

12:39.541 --> 12:40.803
He likes to "chop it up,"
as the kids say.

12:40.847 --> 12:42.022
Wow,
you're doing it again.

12:42.065 --> 12:46.504
Apologize.
Okay, you go right ahead.

12:47.984 --> 12:49.594
I need your help.

12:49.638 --> 12:51.031
With the Bhullars.

12:51.074 --> 12:52.510
Tubb filled me in
on them too.

12:52.554 --> 12:53.903
So you know about Travis.

12:53.947 --> 12:55.992
A little bit.

12:56.036 --> 12:57.211
Let me tell you
something.

12:57.254 --> 12:58.821
I have tangled more
than a few times

12:58.865 --> 13:01.476
with cartel elements
in Texas.

13:01.519 --> 13:03.695
It is nasty business.

13:03.739 --> 13:05.001
So if this boyfriend
of yours --

13:05.045 --> 13:07.961
I think Travis
is gonna kill Veer Bhullar.

13:08.004 --> 13:09.919
And I need to stop it.

13:09.963 --> 13:12.226
You mean "we."

13:13.967 --> 13:17.971
We. You, me,
Deputy, uh, Popcorn.

13:18.014 --> 13:20.060
The team.

13:20.103 --> 13:21.670
So you're not gonna
stop me?

13:21.713 --> 13:24.412
Hell no.

13:24.455 --> 13:25.848
You called a play.

13:25.892 --> 13:27.241
I'm backing that play.

13:27.284 --> 13:30.548
♪♪

13:30.592 --> 13:32.550
Let's go find him.

13:32.594 --> 13:37.860
♪♪

13:37.904 --> 13:39.731
Coming?

13:39.775 --> 13:40.907
Okay.

13:40.950 --> 13:48.131
♪♪

13:48.175 --> 13:50.003
So this is about
my daughter.

13:50.046 --> 13:51.569
What did she put
in your head?

13:51.613 --> 13:53.310
Nothing.

13:53.354 --> 13:54.921
This is about Kate Garza.

13:57.401 --> 13:59.055
I see.

13:59.099 --> 14:00.056
You knew her?

14:00.100 --> 14:01.188
Shut up.

14:03.277 --> 14:05.061
[ Laughs ]

14:06.933 --> 14:09.718
Name your price,
Mr. Stone.

14:09.761 --> 14:11.024
Just --
My name's not Stone.

14:11.067 --> 14:13.113
And I don't want
your money.

14:13.156 --> 14:15.767
What I want is to go have
a little talk somewhere.

14:15.811 --> 14:23.688
♪♪

14:23.732 --> 14:26.300
[ Doorbell rings ]

14:33.002 --> 14:35.265
What are you thinking?Well, that,
if something happened to him,

14:35.309 --> 14:37.050
he's probably not gonna
answer the door.

14:37.093 --> 14:38.703
We could pick the lock.

14:38.747 --> 14:40.053
We could.

14:40.096 --> 14:41.750
Yeah, or you could.

14:41.793 --> 14:44.144
I -- I can't pick locks.

14:44.187 --> 14:46.015
Bad at picking locks?

14:46.059 --> 14:47.060
Mm, terrible at it.

14:47.103 --> 14:48.496
That might
change some things for me.

14:48.539 --> 14:50.019
[ Clattering ]

14:54.110 --> 14:55.416
Or we could go
around back,

14:55.459 --> 14:57.548
see if there's any sign
of forced entry.

14:57.592 --> 14:59.159
You never know. He might have
found the love of his life

14:59.202 --> 15:01.030
and went off
and got married in Vegas.

15:01.074 --> 15:03.380
Is that
what you would do?

15:03.424 --> 15:05.948
No.

15:05.992 --> 15:07.123
But it happens.

15:09.256 --> 15:10.997
Okay.

15:11.040 --> 15:14.000
[ Gate squeaks ]

15:25.620 --> 15:31.539
♪♪

15:31.582 --> 15:37.110
♪♪

15:37.153 --> 15:38.850
Cassie.

15:38.894 --> 15:39.895
Yeah, I see it.

15:39.939 --> 15:45.205
♪♪

15:45.248 --> 15:50.558
♪♪

15:50.601 --> 15:52.212
Mark.

15:52.255 --> 15:53.387
Mark.

15:53.430 --> 16:02.657
♪♪

16:02.700 --> 16:04.485
[ Coughs ]

16:04.528 --> 16:06.139
[ Flies buzzing ]

16:06.182 --> 16:14.234
♪♪

16:14.277 --> 16:22.242
♪♪

16:22.285 --> 16:24.026
This the work
of the Syndicate?

16:24.070 --> 16:25.941
Yeah, it has to be.

16:25.985 --> 16:29.989
♪♪

16:34.167 --> 16:35.646
♪♪

16:35.690 --> 16:37.039
I want the bunny
with the brown spots.

16:37.083 --> 16:39.259
Yeah, well,
you can't have that and a dog.

16:39.302 --> 16:41.522
[ Indistinct conversations ]

16:43.741 --> 16:44.699
Come on, come on.

16:44.742 --> 16:48.442
♪♪

16:48.485 --> 16:50.487
That's the man that made me
drop my milkshake.

16:50.531 --> 16:51.488
It sure is.
Come on.

16:51.532 --> 16:53.273
♪♪

16:53.316 --> 16:55.014
Come on, Phoebe.
Nice and quiet.

16:56.972 --> 16:57.973
[ Door chimes ]

16:58.017 --> 16:59.061
Hey!

16:59.105 --> 17:00.671
Go!
Go, go, go, go!

17:00.715 --> 17:02.195
[ Breathing heavily ]

17:02.238 --> 17:07.504
♪♪

17:07.548 --> 17:12.466
♪♪

17:12.509 --> 17:13.467
Okay.

17:13.510 --> 17:22.215
♪♪

17:22.258 --> 17:23.042
Mom.

17:25.174 --> 17:26.088
Okay.

17:26.132 --> 17:35.315
♪♪

17:35.358 --> 17:37.491
In here.
Here.

17:37.534 --> 17:40.189
Stay here.

17:40.233 --> 17:42.800
♪♪

17:42.844 --> 17:44.063
[ Clattering ]

17:46.978 --> 17:53.115
♪♪

17:53.159 --> 17:54.203
Ahhhh!

17:54.247 --> 17:55.248
[ Grunting, screaming ]

17:55.291 --> 17:57.206
♪♪

17:57.250 --> 17:58.207
[ Screams ]

17:58.251 --> 18:01.167
[ Grunts ]

18:01.210 --> 18:03.125
Ahhhh!

18:03.169 --> 18:05.258
You shouldn't have
followed us!

18:05.301 --> 18:08.652
You'll never be safe.

18:10.176 --> 18:14.397
There are so many more
of me.

18:14.441 --> 18:16.269
[ Breathing heavily,
wheezing ]

18:16.312 --> 18:17.357
[ Grunts ]

18:17.400 --> 18:23.145
♪♪

18:23.189 --> 18:26.148
Phoebe, it's okay.

18:26.192 --> 18:27.802
The bad man
can't hurt us now.

18:27.845 --> 18:29.282
I'm scared!

18:29.325 --> 18:31.240
I don't want to do this
anymore.

18:39.248 --> 18:41.859
[ Sighs ]

18:41.903 --> 18:43.557
[ Cork pops ]

18:43.600 --> 18:46.342
You gonna tell me
what's going on?

18:46.386 --> 18:50.390
Stone -- or Travis,
whatever you wanna call him --

18:50.433 --> 18:51.869
he has my father.

18:53.828 --> 18:55.046
Okay.

18:55.090 --> 18:56.222
They on a hike?

18:56.265 --> 18:58.398
I don't know what
they're doing, but...

18:58.441 --> 19:00.051
it solves a problem
for us.

19:00.095 --> 19:01.314
He's a cop.

19:01.357 --> 19:03.185
We have established this.

19:03.229 --> 19:04.839
This doesn't sound like
a good plan.

19:04.882 --> 19:06.232
Well, you don't know
the whole plan.

19:06.275 --> 19:11.585
Travis is gonna kill
my father.

19:11.628 --> 19:15.023
'Cause he did something
to one of Travis' girlfriends,

19:15.066 --> 19:17.112
blah, blah. Just don't try
to talk me out of it.

19:17.156 --> 19:18.461
I won't.

19:18.505 --> 19:19.984
You know my thoughts
on your father.

19:20.028 --> 19:23.118
Yeah, well,
he's still my father.

19:23.162 --> 19:24.989
What then?

19:25.033 --> 19:26.121
Stone just gets to walk?

19:26.165 --> 19:28.341
No. That's where
you come in.

19:28.384 --> 19:30.212
I've been waiting
for this.

19:30.256 --> 19:31.474
You just give me
the word.

19:31.518 --> 19:33.433
[ Pounding on door ]

19:33.476 --> 19:36.610
♪♪

19:36.653 --> 19:38.220
It's the cops.

19:38.264 --> 19:39.482
Let me think
for a second.

19:39.526 --> 19:42.224
[ Exhales sharply ]

19:42.268 --> 19:44.357
Okay, let them in.

19:44.400 --> 19:46.010
Okay,
and then I kill them?

19:46.054 --> 19:48.448
Mm!
No, just let them in.

19:48.491 --> 19:50.145
♪♪

19:50.189 --> 19:51.277
[ Sighs ]

19:53.409 --> 19:54.584
Hey, nice apron.

19:54.628 --> 19:56.369
Wow.
What is this?

19:56.412 --> 19:58.327
A "Barefoot Contessa" cartel?[ Door closes ]

19:58.371 --> 20:01.374
Oh. Quite the glow-up
on the partner, Jenny Hoyt.

20:01.417 --> 20:02.418
Veer.
Where is he?

20:02.462 --> 20:04.377
Why?

20:04.420 --> 20:05.639
We're here
to arrest him.

20:05.682 --> 20:07.380
We just keep doing this

20:07.423 --> 20:09.382
and you never have
any evidence.

20:09.425 --> 20:12.515
I am very flattered, but maybe
we can skip it this time.

20:12.559 --> 20:14.387
I got a shipping manifest
and a testimony

20:14.430 --> 20:16.867
of a C.I. detailing
your drug trafficking.

20:16.911 --> 20:18.434
Okay.

20:18.478 --> 20:19.870
Go ahead.

20:19.914 --> 20:22.133
You need to leave.

20:22.177 --> 20:23.874
Oh!
Beau: Easy, easy.

20:23.918 --> 20:25.833
[ Choking ]Just breathe into it.

20:25.876 --> 20:27.661
[ Gurgling ]

20:27.704 --> 20:28.966
He's fine.

20:29.010 --> 20:31.621
He's so rugged and direct.

20:31.665 --> 20:33.623
One more time.

20:33.667 --> 20:34.537
Where's Veer?

20:34.581 --> 20:36.322
Stone --

20:36.365 --> 20:37.627
A.K.A. Travis --

20:37.671 --> 20:39.325
he has him.

20:39.368 --> 20:40.935
Do you know what for?

20:40.978 --> 20:43.198
I think you know.

20:44.199 --> 20:45.983
Look, either you tell us
or...

20:46.027 --> 20:48.116
Or what? You're gonna bring me
to the station?

20:48.159 --> 20:50.988
[ Gurgling continues ]No, no. [ Laughs ]
No, no, no, no.

20:51.032 --> 20:53.121
We'll skip that part.
Just take you straight to jail.

20:53.164 --> 20:54.427
Then I'll just ripen up
the tank

20:54.470 --> 20:55.341
with some drunks
and meth heads

20:55.384 --> 20:56.907
and let you make
some real friends.

20:56.951 --> 20:58.996
Then we'll stack
the charges.

21:01.172 --> 21:03.523
Okay. You want him?
Go for it.

21:03.566 --> 21:06.743
Wait, you're -- you're just
gonna give up your father?[ Cellphone clicking ]

21:06.787 --> 21:09.050
Why not?
He'd do the same to me.

21:10.791 --> 21:12.488
This is their location.

21:12.532 --> 21:22.237
♪♪

21:22.281 --> 21:31.812
♪♪

21:31.855 --> 21:41.561
♪♪

21:41.604 --> 21:44.825
Kill me and toss me down there
like an animal.

21:47.741 --> 21:49.351
This country.

21:49.395 --> 21:52.485
You're gonna tell me
what you did with Kate Garza.

21:52.528 --> 21:58.055
♪♪

21:58.099 --> 22:03.452
♪♪

22:09.980 --> 22:18.598
♪♪

22:18.641 --> 22:27.563
♪♪

22:27.607 --> 22:36.398
♪♪

22:36.442 --> 22:45.102
♪♪

22:45.146 --> 22:46.626
Phoebe?

22:48.149 --> 22:50.064
Phoebe...

22:50.107 --> 22:51.674
where's your mom?

22:54.590 --> 22:56.462
I need you to tell me
where she is.

22:58.464 --> 23:02.598
[ Cellphone vibrates ]

23:04.295 --> 23:05.949
This is Cassie.

23:07.516 --> 23:10.563
You were right.

23:10.606 --> 23:12.086
Phoebe deserves more
out of this life.

23:12.129 --> 23:15.437
♪♪

23:15.481 --> 23:17.700
Scarlet, how did you get
in here?

23:17.744 --> 23:19.441
Doesn't matter.

23:19.485 --> 23:21.878
We're capable of anything
when it comes to our kids,

23:21.922 --> 23:24.490
aren't we?

23:24.533 --> 23:26.230
I need you to understand
that I would have done

23:26.274 --> 23:29.146
anything
for my daughter.

23:29.190 --> 23:31.148
That part
was always true.

23:31.192 --> 23:33.716
I understand that.

23:35.283 --> 23:37.111
I have family --

23:37.154 --> 23:38.721
an aunt in Petoskey,
Michigan.

23:38.765 --> 23:40.331
Her number
is in Phoebe's iPad.

23:41.637 --> 23:44.466
I'm asking you,

23:44.510 --> 23:45.989
mother to mother...

23:49.645 --> 23:52.300
...please make sure that Phoebe
ends up in the right hands.

23:54.868 --> 23:56.652
Better hands than mine,
anyway.

23:56.696 --> 23:59.699
Scarlet, you can still do this
the right way.

23:59.742 --> 24:01.570
No, I can't.

24:01.614 --> 24:02.963
Scarlet, wh--

24:03.006 --> 24:05.313
No, I've done something
for you, so...

24:05.356 --> 24:08.055
please,
this is all I ask.

24:08.098 --> 24:09.404
What have you done
for me?

24:09.448 --> 24:10.710
Look inside
Phoebe's backpack.

24:10.753 --> 24:14.496
♪♪

24:14.540 --> 24:16.672
Scarlet.

24:16.716 --> 24:19.066
Scarlet.

24:19.109 --> 24:20.546
[ Grunts ]

24:20.589 --> 24:28.554
♪♪

24:28.597 --> 24:36.562
♪♪

24:36.605 --> 24:44.352
♪♪

24:51.359 --> 24:53.970
Okay,
so I guess this is it?

24:54.014 --> 24:55.668
Sure is.

24:55.711 --> 24:57.147
[ Sliding door opens ]

25:00.150 --> 25:01.761
I brought my tools.

25:01.804 --> 25:03.414
I'm gonna cut
to the chase.

25:03.458 --> 25:04.677
I'm taking over
the entire operation,

25:04.720 --> 25:06.243
and you are going to tell me
everything you know

25:06.287 --> 25:08.158
as financial advisor.

25:08.202 --> 25:12.336
Alright, before we get
to the choppy and stabby part,

25:12.380 --> 25:14.338
can I just make
one last pitch?

25:14.382 --> 25:15.905
Go for it.

25:15.949 --> 25:18.038
Well,
it's not a pitch exactly.

25:18.081 --> 25:20.562
Just something I think
you might want to read.

25:20.606 --> 25:22.738
I think you'll see
that I am much more

25:22.782 --> 25:26.612
than just
a financial advisor.

25:26.655 --> 25:31.486
Veer gave me power of attorney
where the business is concerned.

25:31.530 --> 25:34.794
♪♪

25:34.837 --> 25:36.230
How the hell
did you do this?

25:36.273 --> 25:38.145
Just so you know,
they're real.

25:38.188 --> 25:40.495
'Cause I told him they were
insurance papers for Jag.

25:40.539 --> 25:42.279
And did he read them?
No, of course not.

25:42.323 --> 25:43.846
He's very impatient.

25:44.978 --> 25:46.501
And FYI --

25:46.545 --> 25:48.764
I filed them already
in triplicate.

25:48.808 --> 25:52.594
And I have
a few contingencies --

25:52.638 --> 25:54.596
accounting contingencies --

25:54.640 --> 25:56.903
you know, just in case
I were to end up dead.

25:59.819 --> 26:01.821
What do you want?

26:01.864 --> 26:03.605
Buy me out

26:03.649 --> 26:05.651
or we partner up.

26:05.694 --> 26:08.610
Yeah, I don't think working
together is a great idea.

26:08.654 --> 26:10.177
Okay.

26:10.220 --> 26:11.613
Option "A."

26:11.657 --> 26:15.095
See? I told you us girls
could work this out.

26:17.140 --> 26:18.751
[ Scoffs ]

26:20.796 --> 26:22.624
[ Tires squeal ]

26:22.668 --> 26:25.192
We're gonna be
too late.

26:25.235 --> 26:27.455
No, we're not.I should have done
something sooner.

26:27.498 --> 26:28.848
Hey, hey, come on, now.

26:28.891 --> 26:30.501
Is this the part
where you beat yourself up?

26:30.545 --> 26:32.199
'Cause let's skip that.
Alright?

26:32.242 --> 26:33.896
Some people you just can't save
from themselves.

26:33.940 --> 26:35.332
Trust me, I know that.

26:35.376 --> 26:36.638
And you're gonna want
clean thoughts

26:36.682 --> 26:37.726
going into
whatever this is.

26:37.770 --> 26:38.988
He's making
stupid choices

26:39.032 --> 26:40.424
because he can't
let her go.

26:40.468 --> 26:43.123
Oh! Boy, do I know something
about that.

26:45.691 --> 26:48.128
My, uh -- My ex-wife.

26:48.171 --> 26:50.043
She -- She married
some rich tech dude

26:50.086 --> 26:52.001
who owns a ranch
just south of town.

26:52.045 --> 26:53.916
I followed her up here.

26:53.960 --> 26:55.657
Her and my daughter.

26:55.701 --> 26:57.572
What's this guy's name?
The tech dude?

26:57.616 --> 26:58.747
Avery.

27:00.053 --> 27:01.837
And let me guess,
you're still in love with her?

27:02.969 --> 27:06.886
[ Chuckles ]
You're good.

27:06.929 --> 27:08.714
But, hey, if your plan is
to get me to puddle up over her,

27:08.757 --> 27:09.671
that ain't gonna happen,
alright?

27:09.715 --> 27:11.760
Let's focus
on the job here

27:11.804 --> 27:12.805
and make sure
it don't go sideways.

27:12.848 --> 27:13.588
We're getting close.

27:15.808 --> 27:18.071
♪♪

27:18.114 --> 27:19.725
This is it.

27:19.768 --> 27:25.165
♪♪

27:25.208 --> 27:30.953
♪♪

27:30.997 --> 27:32.259
That's his truck.

27:32.302 --> 27:37.046
♪♪

27:37.090 --> 27:39.701
She deserved better,
you know.

27:39.745 --> 27:43.183
I-I don't understand.

27:43.226 --> 27:44.750
Kate Garza?

27:44.793 --> 27:46.969
Don't --
Don't you say her name.

27:47.013 --> 27:48.144
Don't you say it.

27:50.581 --> 27:51.582
Oh, you.

27:54.194 --> 27:56.849
You're the cop.

27:56.892 --> 27:58.807
The cop that turned Kate
back in Seattle.

27:58.851 --> 28:01.767
What did you think
was gonna happen?

28:01.810 --> 28:05.509
You took my girl's life
in your hands.

28:05.553 --> 28:06.859
You put her in danger.

28:06.902 --> 28:07.947
I did nothing but kill...

28:07.990 --> 28:11.080
No, no, no, no!

28:11.124 --> 28:13.648
She knew
exactly what you were.

28:13.692 --> 28:17.130
She was a waitress
when I met her.

28:17.173 --> 28:19.567
Living a sad,
pointless life.

28:19.610 --> 28:23.092
I opened the world up
for her.

28:23.136 --> 28:25.791
Anything that happened to Kate
happened because of you.

28:25.834 --> 28:28.315
And you -- youare a coward

28:28.358 --> 28:30.621
if you try
and say anything otherwise.

28:30.665 --> 28:32.232
Okay, okay.

28:33.581 --> 28:34.756
Just --
Just tell me something.

28:34.800 --> 28:37.237
What'd you do
with her body?

28:37.280 --> 28:40.806
So many things.

28:40.849 --> 28:42.808
[ Grunts ]

28:42.851 --> 28:45.985
♪♪

28:46.028 --> 28:48.117
[ Breathing heavily ]

28:48.161 --> 28:50.816
It seems you got it wrong.

28:50.859 --> 28:52.992
She was never yours.

28:53.035 --> 28:54.776
You understand?
She was mine.

28:54.820 --> 28:56.822
[ Grunting ]

28:56.865 --> 28:58.824
Mine!

28:58.867 --> 29:01.261
She's still alive.

29:01.304 --> 29:03.872
She's still alive.

29:03.916 --> 29:07.615
♪♪

29:07.658 --> 29:09.008
Wait,
what'd you say?

29:09.051 --> 29:10.226
What'd --
What did you just say?

29:11.837 --> 29:13.055
Kate's alive.

29:14.883 --> 29:16.015
Where is she?

29:16.058 --> 29:18.626
Where -- Where is she?

29:18.669 --> 29:22.064
♪♪

29:22.108 --> 29:23.065
Never.

29:24.632 --> 29:25.807
Where is she?!

29:28.462 --> 29:29.855
Where?!

29:29.898 --> 29:32.031
Come on!
Just say it!

29:33.336 --> 29:34.294
Where is she?!

29:34.337 --> 29:35.382
You tell me!

29:35.425 --> 29:36.949
Where?!

29:36.992 --> 29:38.167
Travis!

29:38.211 --> 29:39.212
Travis, stop!Travis: Where?!

29:39.255 --> 29:41.040
Where?![ Gunshot ]

29:42.693 --> 29:43.956
I won't miss again.

29:43.999 --> 29:45.131
Step away from him now.

29:47.786 --> 29:49.657
On your knees.

29:49.700 --> 29:55.054
♪♪

29:55.097 --> 29:56.446
He's got a pulse,
but it's weak.

29:56.490 --> 29:59.232
♪♪

29:59.275 --> 30:00.929
[ Handcuffs click ]

30:00.973 --> 30:02.235
He hurt her, Jenny.

30:03.889 --> 30:05.978
He hurt her.

30:06.021 --> 30:07.327
It's over.

30:07.370 --> 30:08.894
She's dead.
This is over now, okay?

30:08.937 --> 30:11.461
No. Sh-She's alive.

30:11.505 --> 30:15.857
No. He -- He told me.

30:15.901 --> 30:17.554
She's alive.

30:17.598 --> 30:19.730
Come on.

30:19.774 --> 30:20.688
Help on the way?

30:20.731 --> 30:22.908
On its way.

30:22.951 --> 30:27.477
♪♪

30:33.788 --> 30:35.007
[ Buzzer ]

30:35.050 --> 30:38.010
Doctor said you got there
just in time.

30:38.053 --> 30:40.751
Another blow or two,
Veer Bhullar would've been dead.

30:40.795 --> 30:42.666
He's very lucky.

30:42.710 --> 30:44.494
[ Scoffs ] Well,
that's one way to look at it.

30:44.538 --> 30:46.453
So what's gonna happen
with Travis?

30:46.496 --> 30:47.976
Is he getting charged
with attempted murder?

30:48.020 --> 30:49.325
State wants him back.

30:49.369 --> 30:51.937
Apparently, there's a whole list
of offenses.

30:51.980 --> 30:53.286
Poor son of a bitch.

30:53.329 --> 30:55.157
I'm gonna take him
to his handler.

30:55.201 --> 30:56.898
The meeting's
already set up.

30:56.942 --> 30:59.118
Okay.
You want some company?

30:59.161 --> 31:01.468
No, if that's okay.

31:01.511 --> 31:03.078
Yeah,
that's good by me.

31:05.211 --> 31:06.952
Listen, maybe take him
for a cheeseburger

31:06.995 --> 31:09.302
and a beer on your way.

31:09.345 --> 31:11.521
You know?
One last good thing.

31:13.175 --> 31:14.307
I will.

31:14.350 --> 31:22.054
♪♪

31:22.097 --> 31:29.757
♪♪

31:29.800 --> 31:31.759
Were you gonna shoot me today,
Jenny?

31:35.763 --> 31:37.939
I don't know.

31:37.983 --> 31:39.985
Maybe.

31:42.857 --> 31:44.946
What did Veer tell you
about Kate?

31:44.990 --> 31:46.817
He tortured her.

31:46.861 --> 31:48.950
He...

31:48.994 --> 31:50.778
He broke her.

31:50.821 --> 31:52.998
So why didn't you
kill him?

31:53.041 --> 31:54.390
I was gonna, but...

31:54.434 --> 31:58.220
he said
she's still alive.

31:58.264 --> 32:00.222
How do you know
he wasn't lying?

32:00.266 --> 32:03.182
I don't.

32:16.499 --> 32:19.024
♪ When the air hit my face

32:19.067 --> 32:20.677
What are you doing?

32:22.810 --> 32:23.985
Go find her.

32:24.029 --> 32:25.595
♪ And it smelled like
the truth ♪

32:25.639 --> 32:28.120
You want me to find Kate?
What's the catch?

32:28.163 --> 32:32.080
After you find her,
you will turn yourself in.

32:32.124 --> 32:36.215
♪ I saw you in the lake [ Seatbelt clicks ]

32:36.258 --> 32:38.826
♪ I lay flat on the bed

32:38.869 --> 32:42.569
Go on.

32:42.612 --> 32:47.052
♪ Really cools me off

32:47.095 --> 32:51.056
♪ Keep it dumb, make it soft

32:51.099 --> 32:55.625
♪ Keep it dumb,
make it soft ♪

32:55.669 --> 32:58.106
♪ Watch the water drip

32:58.150 --> 32:59.020
Thank you, Jenny.

32:59.064 --> 33:02.023
Just go
before I change my mind.

33:02.067 --> 33:06.419
♪ From my mouth to yours

33:06.462 --> 33:11.032
♪ I like how you take a sip

33:11.076 --> 33:15.080
♪ I like
how you take a sip ♪

33:15.123 --> 33:21.869
♪ Can you make it light

33:21.912 --> 33:26.439
♪ Break the water
with your arms ♪

33:26.482 --> 33:33.837
♪ Break the water
with your arms ♪

33:33.881 --> 33:40.061
♪♪

33:40.105 --> 33:41.976
[ Cartoon music playing
from TV]

33:42.020 --> 33:47.025
♪♪

33:48.374 --> 33:50.332
Lindor: What's on it?

33:50.376 --> 33:52.117
According to Scarlet,
information on the Syndicate.

33:52.160 --> 33:53.901
You take a peek?
Not yet.

33:53.944 --> 33:55.729
Computer's at the office.

33:55.772 --> 33:57.948
And I need to watch her.

33:57.992 --> 33:59.428
She have any family?

33:59.472 --> 34:01.343
Yeah,
an aunt in Michigan.

34:01.387 --> 34:03.128
Social Services
will have to get involved,

34:03.171 --> 34:04.999
but her aunt said
that she'll look after her.

34:05.043 --> 34:06.261
She jumped on a plane
right away.

34:06.305 --> 34:07.871
She'll be here soon.

34:07.915 --> 34:09.221
Considering everything
she's been through,

34:09.264 --> 34:11.223
she's actually doing
pretty okay.

34:11.266 --> 34:13.486
Would you like
my cookie?

34:13.529 --> 34:15.096
My mom always told me
to share.

34:15.140 --> 34:17.316
No, thanks, sweetie.

34:17.359 --> 34:19.709
Would you?

34:19.753 --> 34:22.190
Maybe just a tiny bite?

34:22.234 --> 34:23.191
Okay.
Okay.

34:25.802 --> 34:27.108
Oh. [ Laughs ]

34:27.152 --> 34:28.457
[ Giggles ]

34:28.501 --> 34:30.372
Mmm.

34:30.416 --> 34:31.721
You're funny.

34:31.765 --> 34:33.245
Don't tell him
that he's funny.

34:33.288 --> 34:35.812
He's not nearly as funny
as he thinks he is.

34:35.856 --> 34:36.813
[ Laughs ]

34:36.857 --> 34:40.295
♪♪

34:40.339 --> 34:42.732
Mm.

34:42.776 --> 34:45.170
So we'll check in
on her all the time.

34:45.213 --> 34:48.216
I made a promise
to Scarlet.

34:48.260 --> 34:49.739
[ Sighs ]
Is that weird?

34:49.783 --> 34:51.132
Not at all.

34:51.176 --> 34:53.352
[ Exhales sharply ]

34:53.395 --> 34:56.137
[ Monitor beeping ]

35:00.315 --> 35:01.621
[ Sighs softly ]

35:06.539 --> 35:07.670
[ Door closes ]

35:08.976 --> 35:12.327
[ Blinds rustle ]

35:27.908 --> 35:29.257
My son.

35:33.653 --> 35:35.263
[ Sighs ]

35:40.094 --> 35:42.401
[ Gasps ]

35:42.444 --> 35:46.056
♪♪

35:46.100 --> 35:48.189
[ Breathing heavily ]

35:48.233 --> 35:52.889
♪♪

35:52.933 --> 35:54.195
[ Muffled screams ]

35:54.239 --> 35:56.241
[ Monitor alarm ]

35:56.284 --> 36:02.247
♪♪

36:02.290 --> 36:07.904
♪♪

36:07.948 --> 36:10.429
[ Flat line ]

36:10.472 --> 36:20.395
♪♪

36:20.439 --> 36:30.405
♪♪

36:30.449 --> 36:32.146
Come on.

36:32.190 --> 36:34.670
[ Door opens ]

36:34.714 --> 36:38.239
♪♪

36:38.283 --> 36:39.284
[ Door closes ]

36:44.767 --> 36:48.162
Tonya: So, you're off?

36:48.206 --> 36:50.338
Alicia: I am.

36:50.382 --> 36:52.122
Where are you going?

36:52.166 --> 36:54.037
London for now.

36:54.081 --> 36:55.430
I've always loved
the rain

36:55.474 --> 36:57.824
and English gardens
in the spring time.

36:57.867 --> 36:59.695
Sounds nice.

36:59.739 --> 37:01.828
Never been there.

37:01.871 --> 37:04.134
You want to come with me?

37:04.178 --> 37:10.140
I'm good right here,
where I was born and raised.

37:11.446 --> 37:14.014
Careful
you don't die here.

37:16.234 --> 37:17.844
Yeah.

37:17.887 --> 37:19.802
I'll watch out for that.

37:21.587 --> 37:26.069
You know,
you remind me of me.

37:26.113 --> 37:28.942
Thanks.

37:28.985 --> 37:30.335
I guess.

37:30.378 --> 37:32.162
[ Chuckles ]

37:32.206 --> 37:33.773
I'd tell you to watch your back
with Ren,

37:33.816 --> 37:36.993
but you already know that.

37:37.037 --> 37:39.779
♪♪

37:39.822 --> 37:42.390
It's been nice getting
to know you.

37:44.697 --> 37:48.353
Oh! I forgot.
Tell Ren I didn't say goodbye.

37:48.396 --> 37:50.224
[ Laughs ]

37:50.268 --> 37:51.704
[ Car door closes ]

37:51.747 --> 37:55.142
♪♪

37:55.185 --> 38:01.017
♪ Happy you are here

38:01.061 --> 38:03.803
♪♪

38:03.846 --> 38:06.153
♪ Everything seems clear

38:06.196 --> 38:08.677
Okay.

38:08.721 --> 38:10.549
Seriously?

38:10.592 --> 38:13.160
You can walk.

38:13.203 --> 38:16.946
[ Sighs ]

38:16.990 --> 38:18.905
[ Scoffs ] Milk it.

38:18.948 --> 38:20.298
Go ahead.

38:21.864 --> 38:27.479
♪ Tell me not to trip
or to lose sight ♪

38:27.522 --> 38:28.480
Don't say it.

38:28.523 --> 38:30.743
[ Sighs ]

38:30.786 --> 38:34.790
♪ You are walking
in my guided light ♪

38:34.834 --> 38:38.228
No, I, uh...

38:38.272 --> 38:39.491
I want to.

38:39.534 --> 38:41.623
[ Sighs ]

38:41.667 --> 38:43.756
♪ Take my hand
and help me not to shake ♪

38:43.799 --> 38:45.366
I love you.

38:45.410 --> 38:46.367
[ Exhales sharply ]

38:46.411 --> 38:51.590
♪ Say I'm alright

38:51.633 --> 38:55.855
♪ I'm alright

38:55.898 --> 39:00.512
♪ Say I'm alright

39:00.555 --> 39:02.165
♪ I'm alright

39:02.209 --> 39:03.645
Barf.

39:03.689 --> 39:04.603
Let's go.

39:04.646 --> 39:09.434
♪ Say I'm alright

39:09.477 --> 39:12.088
♪ I'm alright

39:12.132 --> 39:15.440
[ Sighs ]

39:15.483 --> 39:16.745
Okay, let's see
what we got here.

39:16.789 --> 39:18.399
Uh, account numbers

39:18.443 --> 39:20.619
and it looks like maps
or routes of some kind.

39:20.662 --> 39:21.750
Any names?

39:21.794 --> 39:23.839
Not that I can see.

39:23.883 --> 39:25.667
Yeah, guys,
this is all encrypted.

39:25.711 --> 39:28.670
Feds have experts that can
pretty much unlock anything.

39:28.714 --> 39:30.106
I should send this
to Marshal headquarters

39:30.150 --> 39:31.238
so they can process it.Smart.

39:31.281 --> 39:32.979
See?
Told you he was a keeper.

39:33.022 --> 39:35.982
Mm.
[ Door opens ]

39:36.025 --> 39:38.419
Ooh, girl.
Long day?

39:38.463 --> 39:40.334
Oh, and then some.
What's going on?

39:40.378 --> 39:42.684
Well, Scarlet gave Cassie
a hard drive

39:42.728 --> 39:44.686
with some information
on the Syndicate on it.

39:44.730 --> 39:46.601
Wow. Okay.

39:46.645 --> 39:49.082
Um, anything
we could use?

39:49.125 --> 39:50.300
How 'bout I fill you in
over a beer?

39:50.344 --> 39:51.563
I'm sure we have a lot
to catch up on.

39:51.606 --> 39:53.913
Yeah.

39:53.956 --> 39:56.568
Uh, I'll just stay here
with Denise

39:56.611 --> 39:59.397
and, uh, let you two
have some girl time.

40:00.876 --> 40:02.617
Both: Girl time?

40:02.661 --> 40:06.012
[ Chuckles ] Uh, just go be
with your friend?

40:06.055 --> 40:07.622
I don't know.[ Laughter ]

40:07.666 --> 40:09.581
Aww.

40:09.624 --> 40:11.931
Denise, you're right.
He's a keeper.

40:11.974 --> 40:14.890
[ Laughing ] Girl time.

40:14.934 --> 40:17.023
[ Charley Crockett's
"7 Come 11" plays ]

40:17.066 --> 40:18.720
♪ I rolled into town

40:18.764 --> 40:21.375
♪ And I laid my money down

40:21.419 --> 40:23.725
♪ On a game
that was made to lose ♪

40:23.769 --> 40:25.597
[ Indistinct conversations ]

40:25.640 --> 40:26.815
♪ Everything I had

40:26.859 --> 40:28.600
♪ I could carry on my back

40:28.643 --> 40:30.123
♪ I don't want nothing
I can't use ♪

40:30.166 --> 40:32.517
[ Both laughing ]I mean...

40:32.560 --> 40:35.084
If you told me this morning we'd
be knocking back beers tonight,

40:35.128 --> 40:36.738
I'd be
genuinely surprised.

40:36.782 --> 40:37.826
You know, I thought
that I was gonna be

40:37.870 --> 40:40.394
tailing Scarlet
through Idaho.

40:40.438 --> 40:43.397
And I'm just glad
it's over.
Mm.

40:43.441 --> 40:46.313
Sure you're okay?

40:49.359 --> 40:51.753
All that matters
is that we're here.

40:51.797 --> 40:54.930
Yes, our favorite place
with the pool table.

40:56.192 --> 40:58.107
Yes.We have the juke box.

40:58.151 --> 40:59.892
Oh, don't forget
the tacky light fixtures.

40:59.935 --> 41:01.502
Could never forget those.

41:01.546 --> 41:03.286
[ Both laugh ]

41:03.330 --> 41:04.766
Dewell and Hoyt.Dewell and Hoyt.

41:06.028 --> 41:07.334
Mm.

41:08.814 --> 41:09.728
[ Laughs ]

41:09.771 --> 41:11.381
Of all the bars in town,

41:11.425 --> 41:12.644
I had to pick this one

41:12.687 --> 41:13.775
and crash
your little party.

41:13.819 --> 41:15.211
If you don't mind.

41:15.255 --> 41:16.778
Mm.

41:16.822 --> 41:18.780
First, back it up
and come correct.

41:18.824 --> 41:20.173
Th--Yep, back it up.

41:20.216 --> 41:21.696
Start over.
Back it up.

41:21.740 --> 41:22.784
Alright.

41:22.828 --> 41:25.265
Okay.

41:28.050 --> 41:29.008
Tequila?

41:29.051 --> 41:30.400
Ooh! Hey!

41:30.444 --> 41:32.664
Hey! There you go![ Both laugh ]

41:32.707 --> 41:33.665
Okay. Alright.

41:33.708 --> 41:34.666
Three tequilas.

41:34.709 --> 41:36.581
My friend.

41:36.624 --> 41:37.930
Tres blancos, por favor.

41:37.973 --> 41:40.454
Alright.

41:40.498 --> 41:41.716
So how'd it go?

41:41.760 --> 41:43.805
You know, it went.

41:43.849 --> 41:46.678
Sort of like Travis.

41:48.070 --> 41:50.986
Yeah, um, about that.

41:51.030 --> 41:53.423
Hell, I figured
you'd do something like that.

41:53.467 --> 41:57.079
So are you gonna do anything
about it?

41:59.255 --> 42:01.127
I don't know
what you're talking about.

42:01.170 --> 42:04.913
And if they come asking
questions, I got your back.

42:04.957 --> 42:06.611
It'll give those State
desk jockeys something to do.

42:06.654 --> 42:08.787
[ Laughs ]

42:08.830 --> 42:10.397
Thank you.
Yeah.

42:10.440 --> 42:11.920
Oh! Here we go,
here we go.

42:11.964 --> 42:12.921
Ahh.

42:12.965 --> 42:16.142
Thank you.

42:16.185 --> 42:18.057
Welcome to Montana.

42:18.100 --> 42:19.928
[ Laughs ]
I'll drink to that.

42:19.972 --> 42:24.106
♪♪

